WEBVTT

00:01.420 --> 00:07.420
Believe it or not there are people according to studies that are so hung up on things like email that

00:07.420 --> 00:12.810
they literally check to see if somebody has sent them a message every five to eight minutes.

00:13.030 --> 00:15.870
I would call that obsessive compulsive.

00:15.880 --> 00:21.580
There are times when I don't want to check e-mail but if I'm in my business I'm kind of obligated to

00:21.580 --> 00:22.120
do that.

00:22.300 --> 00:27.490
But what if you're taking a week off to do something maybe it's a business trip and you want to be courteous

00:27.490 --> 00:32.440
to the people that are sending you e-mails who think you're ignoring them by giving them something.

00:32.440 --> 00:33.660
We have all seen.

00:34.120 --> 00:36.520
Hi I'm out of the office I'll be back on.

00:36.670 --> 00:39.750
And when I get back I'll respond to your e-mail kind of message.

00:39.850 --> 00:41.300
Very easy to set up.

00:41.500 --> 00:45.460
Go into G-mail of course go up to our gear and go into settings.

00:45.490 --> 00:49.210
We've been spending a lot of time in settings and that's fine.

00:49.510 --> 00:57.880
It should default to the general down down down until you get to vacation responder It doesn't necessarily

00:57.880 --> 00:58.870
have to be a vacation.

00:58.870 --> 01:01.620
It could be a business trip but we'll go ahead and turn that on.

01:01.990 --> 01:06.550
Now it defaults to the first day today's day and so on going on holiday.

01:06.610 --> 01:08.550
OK when's the last day.

01:08.680 --> 01:15.170
I'm going to put in say the 21st a short hop kind of vacation come in here.

01:15.180 --> 01:17.720
Now the message can be obviously anything you want.

01:17.910 --> 01:21.060
I'll be out of the office until the 21st when I return.

01:21.060 --> 01:23.440
I will respond to your e-mail so leave me alone.

01:24.910 --> 01:26.390
Maybe something like this.

01:26.500 --> 01:28.930
Why would you want to put this in the plain text.

01:28.930 --> 01:33.630
Would it be better if it was on olds and had maybe an image and even a link or something.

01:33.640 --> 01:36.840
Not everybody has the ability to see that stuff.

01:36.970 --> 01:44.920
If I only send the response to people in my contacts or the people in my company one of a kind I know

01:44.920 --> 01:50.740
the browsers they have I know their capabilities but if I'm sending it to anybody that I'm the one off

01:50.740 --> 01:54.750
might send me an e-mail I might want to put that in plain text that's up to you.

01:54.980 --> 01:57.780
I am going to send it to everybody so I'll leave these on check.

01:58.550 --> 02:00.190
And I'll click save changes.

02:01.810 --> 02:09.160
You'll notice a nice bright yellow bar up here which lets me know I'm on vacation settings.

02:09.160 --> 02:14.320
Anybody that e-mails me I will get the e-mail but they will get that response.

02:14.320 --> 02:16.250
Now let's say I get home early.

02:16.630 --> 02:22.470
I can end it now just by clicking here or I can reset it in vacation's settings up to you.

02:22.690 --> 02:23.260
I'm done.

02:23.260 --> 02:24.980
Vacation's over.

02:25.010 --> 02:31.070
So if you need to put an out of office responding messaging it's actually pretty easy and you've got

02:31.070 --> 02:34.340
that big yellow bar at the top reminding you that it's active.
